name: ProtegeExtension
tagline: Support for non-W3C-XML standards to define relations in ontology
body:
### Documentation
https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/12327637/report-owlviz/protege-owlviz.html

### Useful resources
1. Link to install Protege : http://protege.stanford.edu/download/protege/4.3/installanywhere/Web_Installers/ (for only plugin development, building Protege from source is not required though)
2. Instructions given here http://protegewiki.stanford.edu/wiki/PluginAnatomy will get you started with plugin development
3. API reference : link http://protege.stanford.edu/protege/4.3/docs/api/overview-tree.html
